= GNU Screen =

GNU Screen is a very useful tool that multiplexes a physical terminal between several interactive shells. This is very convenient because only one ssh tunnel is required for multiple bash "windows". Online screen resources are very dispersed and disorganized:

  * Advanced Screen Faq [http://www4.informatik.uni-erlangen.de/~jnweiger/screen-faq.html]


While at my WorkPlace in CustomHouse, I always have a PuttySsh instance running, connected to AlephMachine. My screen session is constantly running there, containing running instances of MuttEmail, IrssiIrc (sometimes) and SnowNews. 
